{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"942e98ad-55e4-4e1c-9e70-a6702733e04d","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version          # confirm SDK 11.0.100+ is installed\ndotnet restore            # pull updated packages\ndotnet build              # verify it compiles\ndotnet test               # run tests\n```\n\nAlso review your NuGet packages — any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` references should be bumped to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6f805c12-5c09-46e8-bea6-d1168851bd2a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the three files involved.","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"B82F:E663:17FF84F:1AFD38E:69FD4051"},"id":"fac02d98-3260-43cf-bc43-1eeefc0a58ad","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:46:01.189Z","parentId":"35544a80-82d4-4205-a2c9-4cbbbae0ee94"}
